",{"_":246,"ana":247,"ref":248},{"layout":759},{"p":760,"rs":761,"damage":26},"The Latin text is engraved over two lines (letters c.20 mm high, but of uneven height), to a maximum length of 52 cm.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":763,"dimensions":764}," The letters show some irregularity, with fairly pronounced serifs, and lengthy tails to the letter R. The first two words are separated from the rest by a space; an interpunct is visible at the end of the dedicant’s name, and the final abbreviated phrase is separated from the rest by a large hedera (ivy leaf). The letter I in line 1 is frequently taller than the rest (but so too is the first L in line 1); the final I of line 1 is somewhat irregularly carved.",[765,767,769],{"type":132,"l":133,"from":134,"to":134,"h":766,"unit":136},"18-25",{"type":132,"l":326,"from":139,"to":139,"h":768,"unit":136},"19-23",{"type":143,"l":337,"from":134,"to":139,"h":770,"unit":136},"7-15",{"_":772,"notBefore":773,"notAfter":774,"evidence":563},"Statue can be dated stylistically to the late Antonine period (i.e. the 180s or 190s CE), and the text is compatible with such a date.",180,199,[776,777],{"_":154,"type":155,"ref":156},{"_":158,"type":159,"ref":160,"offset":161},[779],[164,165],[781,782],37.998037,14.262643,{"_":172,"role":173,"ref":174},{"_":785,"type":177},"ME 20194",{"_":277,"mainLang":278,"languages":787},[277],"175724",{"n":184,"url":790,"height":791,"width":792,"desc":367,"surfaceType":189},"ISic000804_tiled.tif","1949px","4512px",[],[192,194,288,795,290,200,202],"Scibona, 2008, Statuary",[204,206,292,797,294,212,214],"EQC3W4UU",[799,800,801,238,755,246,220,221,222,223,220,224,299,278],"isic000804","dedication of a statue to ceres, by iulius acilius hermes, sevir",{"_":12},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Cereri sacr(um) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> Iulius Acilius Her-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>mes · pro honor(e) seviratus ❦ d(eae) d(onum) d(edit) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":804,"ptr":805,"ref":806,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"19 no.9 fig.1-2",{"target":230},{"_":232,"target":232},{"file":808,"uri":808,"title":809,"status":810,"editionAuthor":13,"type":811,"objectType":812,"material":813,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":815,"handNote":818,"date":825,"places":829,"geo":832,"provenance":154,"provenanceGeo":834,"country":169,"region":170,"settlement":154,"repository":837,"idno":838,"textLang":840,"tmNumber":842,"facsimile":843,"letterHeights":846,"publications":847,"zotero":848,"keywords":849,"html":853,"bibl":854},"ISic000805","Fragmentary latin inscription mentioning a proconsul",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":311,"ana":312,"ref":313},{"_":814,"ana":247,"ref":248},"marble (pink)",{"layout":816},{"rs":817,"damage":26},{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":819,"dimensions":820},"Letters are 50mm high, tall, thin, serifed. P and R are open; the hastae of M join early and extend upwards; a hedera like interpunct (tail top and bottom to a hollow element) appears once between C and V of line 2.",[821,824],{"type":132,"l":822,"from":134,"to":330,"h":823,"unit":136},"Line 1-3","50",{"type":143,"l":259,"from":134,"to":139,"unit":136},{"_":826,"notBefore":827,"notAfter":828,"precision":151},"3rd century CE",201,300,[830,831],{"_":154,"type":155,"ref":156},{"_":158,"type":159,"ref":160,"offset":161},[833],[164,165],[835,836],37.998054,14.262639,{"_":172,"role":173,"ref":174},{"_":839,"type":177},"ME 20228",{"_":277,"mainLang":278,"languages":841},[277],"175725",{"n":184,"url":844,"height":845,"width":635,"desc":636,"surfaceType":189},"ISic000805_tiled.tif","5256px",[],[192,194,288,197,198,200,202],[204,206,292,209,210,212,214],[850,851,852,15,311,814,220,221,222,223,220,224,299,278],"isic0